// Vitest Snapshot v1, https://vitest.dev/guide/snapshot.html

exports[`Coach Renderer > celebrates perfect score > perfect-score 1`] = `
"Score: 100/100
Flawless. Your CLI actually talks back. I'm almost proud.

Nothing to fix. Go ship it."
`;

exports[`Coach Renderer > roasts H1 + H2 failures with actionable fixes > h1-fail-h2-fail 1`] = `
"Score: 0/100
Yikes. Your CLI is so quiet I can hear the tokens screaming in agony.

H1 · Line Count · FAIL
Your SKILL.md is 457 lines. The budget is 150.
→ This is not a SKILL.md, it's a manifesto. Delete 307 lines minimum. Move every \\"if the tool returns X, do Y\\" paragraph into the tool's response as a hint.

H2 · Hint Coverage · FAIL
1 tool(s) have zero fixtures. They don't speak at all: search
→ Add talking-cli-fixtures for [search]. One error scenario, one empty/zero-result scenario. Make them return a \\"hints\\" field.
1 tool(s) are half-covered: write
→ Check which scenario is missing (error vs empty-result) and add the missing fixture.

---
Fix the issues above, then run npx talking-cli audit again to see your new score."
`;
